\angle AED &= 180^{\circ}-\angle ADE-\angle EAD \\
&= 180^{\circ}-132^{\circ}-30^{\circ} \\
&= 18^{\circ}.
\end{align*} Since $\angle AEB$ is a straight angle,  \begin{align*}
\angle DEB &= 180^{\circ}-\angle AED \\
&= 180^{\circ}-18^{\circ} \\
&= 162^{\circ}.
